data.enText: wrong; not as it should be

data.chText: 她觉得有点不对头，就叫了警察。
data.enText: She sensed something was amiss and called the police.

data.chText: 并非不称心；并非不顺当
data.enText: to be useful or pleasant in a particular situation

data.chText: 此刻若交点好运就好了。
data.enText: A little luck wouldn't go amiss right now!
to feel offended by sth, perhaps because you have understood it in the wrong way

data.chText: 我要是主动提出帮助，她会不会见怪？
data.enText: Would she take it amiss if I offered to help?

tr: in an imperfect or faulty way
example: Miss Bennet would not play at all amiss if she practiced more"- Jane Auste

tr: in an improper or mistaken or unfortunate manner
example: if you think him guilty you judge amiss
no one took it amiss when she spoke frankly

tr: away from the correct or expected course
example: something has gone awry in our plans
something went badly amiss in the preparations

value.def: If you say that something is amiss, you mean there is something wrong.

example.ex: Their instincts warned them something was amiss...
example.tran: 他们直觉上感到有什么地方不对劲儿。

example.ex: Something is radically amiss in our health care system.
example.tran: 我们的保健制度存在重大缺陷。

value.tran: 不对的；不正常的；错误的

value.def: If you say that something would not go amiss or would not come amiss, you mean that it would be pleasant and useful.

example.ex: A bit of charm and humour would not go amiss...
example.tran: 人有点吸引力和幽默感总是好的。

example.ex: The cracks are showing in the walls and a lick of paint would not come amiss.
example.tran: 墙面开始出现裂缝了，刷一点油漆就能补好。

value.tran: 会起作用；会称心如意；不会出错
